The first Civilian Governor of old Kaduna State, Alhaji Balarabe Musa, is dead. His death was confirmed Wednesday morning by a leading member of his People’s Redemption Party (PRP), Senator Shehu Sani. Musa, a left-wing politician, was elected Governor of Kaduna during the Second Republic. He held office from October 1979 until he was impeached on 23 June, 1981. Born 21 August 1936, the elderstateman died in Kaduna at 84. Details shortly….